parameters: Sir, we haven't finished with the investigation.
Tin Can... don't you think this house looked completely different
As a matter of ... "matter" in it? I calculated this version
having 33.7455588229333 percent less mass than the first one.
A whopping 15.99998 percent less compared to the second.
If compared with with the mass represented by an average
house from our Home World, Sir, this is 64 percent less massive.
Oh, a mere round number? 64 percent? I'm surprised!
No need of surprise here, Captain. According to the
density of the Galaxy in which we live compared with this..
No no no no.... no! Dreamborn!
No need to go into these details. I just wanted to point out
I can feel this house is emptier.
This is what I tried to state the whole time, Sir.
I detect multiple gamma emissions Sir, like in the previous house.
But I can't pin point their exact locations.
Few things packed in here. Everything looks like
wrapped in some sort of plastic film.
More wrapped objects in here. A tiny little squared box.
Sir, I do not find any other interference in this place.
Perhaps it is time to review the data.
A doll. A label on it says: Handsome guy!
This version of the doll looks sad!
There is nothing more to collect here, Sir.
How can I assist you, Sir?
You see Dreamborn... they looked like a nice couple.
It seemed to me they had good friends, good time together.
Why she had to go away?
I wonder what all of this has to do with the artifact.
You cannot see the potential still, but you feel it, Captain.
Where are you? Why are you showing me all of this?
There is a reason for everything.
You being here, right now. Your companion and its abilities.
Do you believe in fate? Do you believe that things
should have a natural way of occurring?
This is still not done. Feel this emptiness.
Well, well, well Captain. You get the next trophy.
Eeeh... this "Shinigami" will drive me crazy!
